OL,3,C'Plonker, prat and numpty': Study
OL,4,Cshows classic British insults dying out
OL,6,FA new study suggests British insults
OL,7,Fsuch as berk, nitwit, pillock and
OL,8,Fplonker are set to die out as many
OL,9,Fyoung people have never heard of them
OL,11,FClassic British insults such as
OL,12,F"pillock", "plonker" and "git" could
OL,13,Fsoon be on their way out, as Gen Z
OL,14,Fembrace newer terms like "basic",
OL,15,F"Karen" and "simp".
OL,17,FA new survey of Gen Zs - those born
OL,18,Fbetween 1997 and 2012 - has found that
OL,19,Fsix in ten of the demographic have not
OL,20,Fheard the insult "berk" meaning an
OL,21,F"idiot".
