OL,3,C'Plonker, prat and numpty': Study
OL,4,Cshows classic British insults dying out
OL,6,FThe posh slang term "blighter", to
OL,7,Fdescribe a contemptible individual,
OL,8,Fwas unknown to a majority (54%) of the
OL,9,F18 to 29 year olds surveyed.J"Language
OL,10,Fchanges, evolves and moves on," said
OL,11,FHarriet Scott, CEO of research agency
OL,12,FPerspectus Global.
OL,14,F"Our research shows that calling
OL,15,Fsomeone a plonker or a prat is no
OL,16,Flonger a fashionable way to insult
OL,17,Fthem.
